# Track 3: Watcher administration and species of Earth

**Bottom line up front.** Seven traditions, examined in original languages, converge on a remarkably consistent picture: a tiered cosmos (Q15) administered by ranked beings whose distinctions appear to be **species AND functions** simultaneously (Q16); a parallel subterranean cosmography populated by non-human sentients (Q17); a quantified administrative scale built on the numbers **70/72 (territorial) and 200 (military) and 2-4 (per-person)** (Q18); a multi-layered Arabic pre-Adamic taxonomy of at least four named species plus 28 nations (Q19); a cross-tradition "Watcher technology" of detachable luminous credentials — *melammu / xvarenah / kāvôd / sakīna / tejas* — that physically marks and authorizes administrative office (Q20); and a textually-formalized **two-tier diagnostic** distinguishing embodied administrator-deities from a transcendent uncontainable Source (Q21). The traditions themselves preserve and, through their most rigorous schools (Ibadi, Mu'tazilite, Maimonidean, Advaita), formalize precisely the split this project hypothesized.

