## Q20 — Melammu, xvarenah, kāvôd, sakīna, tejas: one phenomenon, five vocabularies

**Akkadian *melammu*** (Sumerian loanword ME-LÁM) is glossed in CAD M/2 as *"awe-inspiring luminosity, supernatural sheen emanating from gods, demons, kings, temples."* Crucially, it is **both worn and generated**. The full verbal range includes *labāšu* (to clothe in), *našû* (to bear/carry), *katāmu* (to cover — Anzu II.37: *"melammū-šu šadâ iktum"* "his melammu covered the mountain"), *malû* (to fill — paralleling Hebrew *mlʾ* in Isa 6:3), *tabālu* (to carry off), *šaḥāṭu* (to strip off), and the diagnostic combination in **Enūma Eliš I.67-68**: *"išḫuṭ-ma agā-šu melamme-šu itbal / ramā-nuš u-ʾaddir-šu"* — Marduk **strips Apsû's crown, carries off his melammu, and clothes himself in it**. The Hammurabi Code epilogue invokes Anu to "deprive (the offender) of the *melam šarrūtim*" — the *melammu of kingship* is detachable by divine fiat. The associated *puluḫtu* is its affective complement: the terror it inspires.

**Avestan *xvarenah* (xᵛarənah)** functions identically. **Yašt 19.31-38** (Zamyād Yašt) narrates the **three flights from Yima** when he utters the *draoɣəm vacim* (false word): the Glory departs *"mərəɣahe kəhrpa"* — "in the shape of a Varəɣna bird." Sequence: **Mithra catches the first flight; Thraetaona (Θraētaona) the second; Keresaspa (Kərəsāspa) the third.** Loss of xvarenah = loss of kingship; Yima becomes *brāsat̰* (trembling, terrified) and is hunted by Aži Dahāka, who takes his throne. The xvarenah is **physical, visible (as a bird), detachable, transferable, and forfeit-on-falsehood**. Pahlavi *xwarrah* → New Persian **farr / farrah** survives in Sasanian iconography as the flame-halo behind the royal head.

**Sanskrit siddhis** (Patañjali Yoga-Sūtra 3.45 verbatim: *"tato 'ṇimādi-prādurbhāvaḥ kāya-sampat tad-dharmānabhighātaś ca"*) enumerate eight: *aṇimā* (atomic minuteness), *mahimā* (infinite magnitude), *laghimā* (weightlessness), *garimā* (infinite heaviness), *prāpti* (reaching anywhere), *prākāmya* (irresistible will), *īśitva* (lordship), *vaśitva* (control of all beings). Bhāgavata 11.15.4-5 substitutes *kāmāvasāyitā* for *garimā* in its octet and adds ten secondary siddhis (far-hearing, far-seeing, body-entry, dying at will, foreknowledge of past/present/future, mind-reading, immunity to fire/sun/water/poison). Kṛṣṇa explicitly calls them *autpattika* — "innate to Me" — and at 11.15.33-34 declares them *antarāyāḥ* (impediments) to *yoga uttama* and *kāla-kṣapaṇa-hetavaḥ* (causes of wasting time). **The siddhis are simultaneously real human achievements via yoga AND intrinsic divine/Watcher-level capacities that the yogin participates in by *dhāraṇā* on the Lord** (*siddhi-da*, 11.15.2).

**Tejas** (Gita 7.10, 10.36, 15.12 — *"tejas tejasvinām aham…tat tejo viddhi māmakam"*) and **ojas** (Rig Veda; Caraka 17.74-75; Suśruta 15.19-25) supply the vital-luminous register. **Hebrew *kāvôd*** (Exod 24:17: *"kĕvôd YHWH kĕ-ʾēš ʾōkhelet"* — "the appearance of the kavod of YHWH was like a devouring fire"; Ezek 1:27-28: glowing *ḥashmal* amber surrounded by rainbow nimbus) and **Aramaic *shekhīnah*** continue the same complex. **Aster's *The Unbeatable Light* (2012) demonstrates direct philological borrowing**: Akkadian *katāmu* and *malû* with melammu correspond precisely to Hebrew *ksh* (Hab 3:3) and *mlʾ* (Isa 6:3) with *kāvôd*, during the 8th-7th century BCE Assyrian contact period. **Greek *doxa*** in the Septuagint renders *kāvôd*; the NT Transfiguration (Mt 17:2 *"elampsen to prosōpon autou hōs ho hēlios"*) and 2 Cor 3:18 (*"apo doxēs eis doxan"*) inherit the full complex.

**Arabic *nūr*** (Q 24:35 *"Allāhu nūru s-samāwāti wa-l-arḍ"*) and **sakīna** (Q 2:248, in the Ark of the Covenant; 48:4, 18, 26) extend the schema into Islam. **Suhrawardī's *Ḥikmat al-Ishrāq* (12th c.) explicitly identifies sakīna with the ancient Iranian *kayan khvarrah***, recognizing the cross-tradition continuity. The Sufi/Shīʿī **nūr Muḥammadī** — the pre-existent Light transmitted through the prophetic line — is structurally identical to xvarenah passing through legitimate rulers.

**Synthesis.** The structural identity is too specific to be coincidence: (1) **detachable visible aura** marking legitimate office; (2) **transferability** by gift, strip, theft, donning; (3) **forfeiture on transgression** — Yima's lie, Adam's loss of glory (1QS 4.5; CD III.19-20), the Hammurabi-curse, the Temple's emptying in Ezekiel 10; (4) **bird/flight motif** (Varəɣna falcon, Anzu, Sakīna-cloud); (5) **terror in beholders** (puluḫtu / yirʾah / awe). The Akkadian-Hebrew and Indo-Iranian-Arabic chains are documented historical transmissions; the Sanskrit *tejas* shares the Indo-Iranian root cluster; *siddhis* are the **operational/technical powers** that the radiance is the *credential* of.

**Best-fit hypothesis: a single underlying phenomenon — a physically real, perceptible, transferable credential of administrative office in a divine hierarchy — described in five overlapping vocabularies.** This is the Watcher-technology signature. **Confidence VH** for melammu↔xvarenah↔kāvôd↔doxa; **H** for sakīna/nūr inclusion; **M** for siddhis as identical (better classified as the *powers* the radiance authorizes).

